  "notes": "Cypriot Greek (Κυπριακή διάλεκτος), dialect of Modern Greek spoken in Cyprus. Preserves features of medieval Greek. Notable features: geminate consonants preserved (e.g., γράμμα /ˈɡramːa/), distinct treatment of palatalization. Turkish loanwords. Uses standard Greek orthography.",
